(61, 214, 'Tue Mar 24 03:24:20 +1100 2015', 'Tue Mar 24 03:24:20 +1100 2015', 'gs-custom-autocomplete-input', 'GS Custom Autocomplete Input', 'GS Custom Autocomplete helps you easily add on your website one or more input fields that will help the user with some autocomplete hints. There are 3 ways to use data with the autocomplete module:\n\n\n	<pre>-  Using a datalist tag\n-  Importing the object from an external JSON file\n-  Querying the server for new data on each input change</pre>\n\n\n	Here are the main features of the GS Autocomplete module:\n &ndash;  No jQuery!\n &ndash;  Light weight JavaScript\n &ndash;  Fully customised dropdown\n &ndash;  Easy to implement\n &ndash;  Add as many autocomplete inputs on a page as you like\n &ndash;  Use different methods to grab data: JSON files, datalist tag, server-side scripting\n &ndash;  Fully customise the dropdown look and feel\n &ndash;  Navigate trough options using up / down arrows', 'http://codecanyon.net/theme_previews/10876621-gs-custom-autocomplete-input', 'https://0.s3.envato.com/files/127245545/landing.png', 'http://codecanyon.net/item/gs-custom-autocomplete-input/10876621', 'http://codecanyon.net/item/gs-custom-autocomplete-input/full_screen_preview/10876621', 5, 'autocomplete, autocomplete input, custom autocomplete, custom results, form autocomplete, input hint, input suggestions, instant results, search hints', 0, 0, 0),
(62, 214, 'Mon Mar 23 01:35:49 +1100 2015', 'Mon Mar 23 01:35:49 +1100 2015', 'video-feed-flow-gallery-exension', 'Video Feed - Flow Gallery Exension', '<h3 id="item-description__flow-gallery-jquery-plugin-available-here"><a href="http://codecanyon.net/item/flow-gallery-html5-multimedia-gallery/10741414">Flow Gallery jQuery plugin available here</a></h3>\n\n	<strong>Video Feed</strong> is an <strong>extension or add-on</strong> for the <a href="http://codecanyon.net/item/flow-gallery-html5-multimedia-gallery/10741414"><strong>Flow Gallery</strong></a> jQuery plugin. This extension allows you to pull feeds from <strong>Youtube</strong>, <strong>Vimeo</strong> and <strong>Dailymotion</strong> in order to build your gallery. <strong>All the settings</strong> of the <strong>Flow Gallery</strong> plugin can be used with this extension.\n\n\n	<strong>NOTE:</strong> you need to have the <strong>Flow Gallery plugin</strong> in order for this extension to work.\n\n\n<h3 id="item-description__the-key-features-are"><strong>The key features are:</strong></h3>\n<li>Pull videos from Youtube based on <strong>text search</strong>, <strong>user ID</strong>, or <strong>playlist</strong>.</li>\n\n    <li>Pull videos from Vimeo based on <strong>user ID</strong>, <strong>album</strong>, or <strong>channel</strong>.</li>\n\n    <li>Pull videos from Dailymotion based on <strong>user ID</strong>, <strong>channel</strong>, <strong>group</strong>, or <strong>playlist</strong>.</li>\n\n    <li>Video <strong>duration</strong>, <strong>upload date</strong> and <strong>views</strong> are shown for each item in the gallery.</li>\n\n    <li>Sort items based on their <strong>upload date</strong>, <strong>ratings</strong>, <strong>views</strong>, <strong>duration</strong>, as well as title.</li>\n\n    <li>Filter videos based on the availability of <strong>HD version</strong> and being of <strong>long</strong> or <strong>short duration</strong>.</li>\n\n    <li>Item <strong>titles</strong> and <strong>descriptions</strong> are pulled from Youtube/Vimeo/Dailymotion. </li>\n\n    <li>Cache feed data for faster loading of gallery and prevent crossing API call limit.</li>\n\n    <li><strong>All settings/options</strong> of the <strong>Flow Gallery</strong> jQuery plugin can be used.</li>\n<h3 id="item-description__configurable-options-are"><strong>Configurable options are:</strong></h3>\n<li>Choose between either &ndash; <strong>Youtube</strong>, <strong>Vimeo</strong> or <strong>Dailymotion</strong> feeds.</li>\n\n                <li>Items can be sorted, using the Sort menu, by their upload date, ratings, views, duration, as well as titles.</li>\n\n                <li>Items can be filtered based on the videos being either of long or short duration, and on the availability of HD version.</li>\n\n                <li>Youtube feeds can be pulled based on <strong>text string</strong>, <strong>user ID</strong>, or a <strong>playlist</strong>.</li>\n\n                <li>Option to specify the number of items to pull from Youtube.</li>\n\n                <li>Vimeo feeds can be pulled based on <strong>user ID</strong>, <strong>album</strong> or <strong>channel</strong>.</li>\n\n                <li>Option to specify the number of items to pull from Vimeo.</li>\n\n                <li>Dailymotion feeds can be pulled based on <strong>user ID</strong>, <strong>channel</strong>, <strong>group</strong> or <strong>playlist</strong>.</li>\n\n                <li>Option to specify the number of items to pull from Dailymotion.</li>\n<h3 id="item-description__special-notes"><strong>Special Notes</strong></h3>\n<li>This is an extension for the <strong>Flow Gallery jQuery plugin</strong>, so you will need that plugin in order to use this extension.</li>\n    <li>Only <strong>public</strong> videos are pulled from Youtube/Vimeo/Dailymotion.</li>\n    <li>If you have any query regarding any feature of this extension before purchasing then please post your query in the comments section and I will get back to you as soon as possible.</li>\n<h3 id="item-description__more-items-by-cosmocoder">More Items by CosmoCoder</h3>\n<a href="http://codecanyon.net/item/nova-gallery-responsive-html5-mutimedia-gallery/3766022"><img src="http://0.s3.envato.com/files/45124196/novagallery-preview.jpg" alt="Nova Gallery - Responsive HTML5 Multimedia Gallery"></a>\n<br><br><a href="http://codecanyon.net/item/ccgallery-html5-multimedia-gallery/233741"><img src="http://1.s3.envato.com/files/35542452/ccgallery-preview.jpg" alt="CCGallery - HTML5 Multimedia Gallery"></a>\n<br><br><a href="http://codecanyon.net/item/vimuse-html5-media-player/7847349"><img src="https://0.s3.envato.com/files/115695856/vimuse-preview.jpg" alt="Vimuse - HTML5 Media Player"></a>', 'http://codecanyon.net/theme_previews/10872403-video-feed-flow-gallery-exension', 'https://0.s3.envato.com/files/127196255/flowgallery-videofeed-preview.jpg', 'http://codecanyon.net/item/video-feed-flow-gallery-exension/10872403', 'http://codecanyon.net/item/video-feed-flow-gallery-exension/full_screen_preview/10872403', 8, 'channel, dailymotion, extension, flow gallery, gallery, jquery, material design, playlist, plugin, video, vimeo, youtube', 0, 0, 0),
(63, 214, 'Fri Mar 20 02:07:14 +1100 2015', 'Fri Mar 20 02:07:14 +1100 2015', 'responsive-grid', 'Responsive Grid', 'In the modern world of responsive web design tables can often cause a particular problem for designers due to their row based layout. Responsive Grid resolves that problem by optimizing the table&rsquo;s layout for different screen sizes.\nKey features include:\nExtend your responsive design to HTML tables\nCollapsed information from the table shown in a child row', 'http://codecanyon.net/theme_previews/10769312-responsive-grid', 'https://0.s3.envato.com/files/126696998/Project1__1426271284_202.88.235.192.jpg', 'http://codecanyon.net/item/responsive-grid/10769312', 'http://codecanyon.net/item/responsive-grid/full_screen_preview/10769312', 7, 'css, grid, html, jquery, responsive, table', 0, 0, 0),
(64, 214, 'Fri Mar 20 02:04:44 +1100 2015', 'Fri Mar 20 02:04:44 +1100 2015', 'sr-transition', 'SR-Transition', '<strong>SR-Transition</strong> is a jQuery based script which allows smooth transitions from page to page within a website using your basic options of a circle shape mask or fade. The Goal behind creating this script was to achieve a great transition animation with ease of use and implementation.\n\n<li><strong>Supports Form Submission</strong> &ndash; Through the options, you&rsquo;re able to specify the selectors for submit buttons. This way, the transitions are handled via post.</li>\n\n<li><strong>Two Available Transitions</strong> &ndash; You have the option of choosing between a circle mask transition or a simple fade effect. The fade effect is more of a neutral transition which can be used with any theme or style.</li>\n\n<li><strong>Custom CSS Classes</strong> &ndash; Want or need a unique css property added to the view wrapper? Use the available options to add your custom class.</li>\n\n<li><strong>Unique Safari Mobile Support</strong> &ndash; Apple loves to set their own trends. On Safari mobile, when a user is scrolling down, you&rsquo;ll notice the back and forward buttons tend to disappear. This creates a problem when displaying your content using height:100% &amp; overflow:auto. So the script detects when you&rsquo;re using Safari on a mobile device to include some special treatment.</li>\n<h3 id="item-description__requirements">Requirements</h3>\n\nThis script requires a server/virtual server including the listed dependencies below.\n\n<h3 id="item-description__dependencies">Dependencies</h3>\n\n<li><strong><a href="http://jquery.com/" rel="nofollow">jQuery</a></strong> &ndash; jQuery is a fast, small, and feature-rich JavaScript library. It makes things like HTML document traversal and manipulation, event handling, animation, and Ajax much simpler with an easy-to-use API that works across a multitude of browsers.</li>\n\n<li><strong><a href="https://github.com/browserstate/history.js/" rel="nofollow">HistoryJS</a></strong> &ndash; History.js gracefully supports the HTML5 History/State APIs (pushState, replaceState, onPopState) in all browsers.</li>\n\n<li><strong><a href="https://github.com/jquery/jquery-color" rel="nofollow">jQuery Color</a></strong> &ndash; jQuery plugin for color manipulation and animation support.</li>\nDependencies already included.', 'http://codecanyon.net/theme_previews/10803617-srtransition', 'https://0.s3.envato.com/files/126696721/envato.item.preview.jpg', 'http://codecanyon.net/item/srtransition/10803617', 'http://codecanyon.net/item/srtransition/full_screen_preview/10803617', 8, 'ajax, animation, fade, javascript, jquery, pushstate, transitions', 0, 0, 0),
(65, 214, 'Sat Mar 21 06:01:26 +1100 2015', 'Tue Mar 24 02:29:58 +1100 2015', 'ideabox-multipurpose-step-form', 'Ideabox - Multipurpose Step Form', '<h4 id="item-description__main-features">Main Features</h4>\n    <ol><li>Modern</li>\n        <li>Flat</li>\n        <li>Responsive</li>\n        <li>Easy Install</li>\n        <li>5 Color Shemes</li>\n        <li>6 cell grid system</li>\n        <li>Clean Design</li>\n        <li>Form Validation (requred, email,number and confirm validation included)</li>\n        <li>Jquery plugin</li>\n    </ol><br><br><h4 id="item-description__watch-the-video-for-install">Watch the video for Install</h4>\n<br><br><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Gjry7i8yE84" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://tevratgundogdu.com/works/stepsform/trash/video_img.jpg"></a>', 'http://codecanyon.net/theme_previews/10818199-ideabox-multipurpose-step-form', 'https://0.s3.envato.com/files/127392491/steps-form-image.jpg', 'http://codecanyon.net/item/ideabox-multipurpose-step-form/10818199', 'http://codecanyon.net/item/ideabox-multipurpose-step-form/full_screen_preview/10818199', 6, 'jquery steps form, multi step form, multipurpose step form, Step Form, step form plugin', 0, 0, 0),
(66, 214, 'Thu Mar 19 01:46:25 +1100 2015', 'Thu Mar 19 01:46:25 +1100 2015', 'photo-feed-flow-gallery-exension', 'Photo Feed - Flow Gallery Exension', '<h3 id="item-description__flow-gallery-jquery-plugin-available-here"><a href="http://codecanyon.net/item/flow-gallery-html5-multimedia-gallery/10741414">Flow Gallery jQuery plugin available here</a></h3>\n\n	<strong>Photo Feed</strong> is an <strong>extension or add-on</strong> for the <a href="http://codecanyon.net/item/flow-gallery-html5-multimedia-gallery/10741414"><strong>Flow Gallery</strong></a> jQuery plugin. This extension allows you to pull feeds from <strong>Flickr</strong> and <strong>Picasa</strong> in order to build your gallery. <strong>All the settings</strong> of the <strong>Flow Gallery</strong> plugin can be used with this extension.\n\n\n	<strong>NOTE:</strong> you need to have the <strong>Flow Gallery plugin</strong> in order for this extension to work.\n\n\n<h3 id="item-description__the-key-features-are"><strong>The key features are:</strong></h3>\n<li>Pull <strong>photos/videos</strong> from Flickr based on <strong>text search</strong>, <strong>tags</strong>, <strong>user ID</strong>, <strong>set</strong>, <strong>group</strong>, or <strong>collection</strong>.</li>\n\n    <li>Pull <strong>photos/videos</strong> from Picasa based on <strong>text search</strong>, <strong>user ID</strong>, <strong>album</strong>, or <strong>collection</strong>.</li>\n\n    <li>Sort items based on their <strong>post/upload date</strong>, as well as title.</li>\n\n    <li>Specify the <strong>size</strong> of the <strong>thumbnails</strong> and <strong>large images</strong> that are to be pulled.</li>\n\n    <li>Option to specify the <strong>number of albums/sets</strong> to show in a <strong>collection</strong>. </li>\n\n    <li>Item <strong>titles</strong> and <strong>descriptions</strong> are pulled from Flickr/Picasa. </li>\n\n    <li>Cache feed data for faster loading of gallery and prevent crossing API call limit.</li>\n\n    <li><strong>All settings/options</strong> of the <strong>Flow Gallery</strong> jQuery plugin can be used.</li>\n<h3 id="item-description__configurable-options-are"><strong>Configurable options are:</strong></h3>\n<li>Choose between either &ndash; <strong>Flickr</strong> or <strong>Picasa</strong> feeds.</li>\n\n                <li>Items can be sorted, using the Sort menu, by their post/upload date, as well as titles.</li>\n\n                <li>Flickr feeds can be pulled based on <strong>text string</strong>, <strong>tags</strong>, <strong>user ID</strong>, <strong>set</strong>, <strong>group</strong>, or a <strong>collection</strong>.</li>\n\n                <li>Option to specify the number of items to pull from Flickr.</li>\n\n                <li>In case of a Flickr Collection you can choose to show all the albums/sets or a specific number.</li>\n\n                <li>You can choose how to sort the images that are pulled from Flickr, such as <strong>date of post</strong>, <strong>date taken</strong>, <strong>interestingness</strong> and <strong>relevance</strong>.</li>\n\n                <li>You can specify the thumbnail size and the large image size that are to be pulled from Flickr.</li>\n\n                <li>You also have the option to either pull <strong>photos</strong>, or <strong>videos</strong> or <strong>both</strong>.</li>\n\n                <li>Picasa feeds can be pulled based on <strong>text string</strong>, <strong>user ID</strong>, <strong>album</strong> or <strong>collection</strong>.</li>\n\n                <li>In case of a Picasa Collection you can choose to show all the albums or a specific number.</li>\n\n                <li>Option to specify the number of items to pull from Picasa.</li>\n\n                <li>You can specify the thumbnail size and the large image size that are to be pulled from Picasa.</li>\n<h3 id="item-description__special-notes"><strong>Special Notes</strong></h3>\n<li>This is an extension for the <strong>Flow Gallery jQuery plugin</strong>, so you will need that plugin in order to use this extension.</li>\n    <li>In order to pull feeds from Flickr you will need to get a <strong>Flickr API Key.</strong></li>\n    <li>Only <strong>public</strong> photos and videos are pulled from Flickr and Picasa.</li>\n    <li>If you have any query regarding any feature of this extension before purchasing then please post your query in the comments section and I will get back to you as soon as possible.</li>\n<h3 id="item-description__more-items-by-cosmocoder">More Items by CosmoCoder</h3>\n<a href="http://codecanyon.net/item/nova-gallery-responsive-html5-mutimedia-gallery/3766022"><img src="http://0.s3.envato.com/files/45124196/novagallery-preview.jpg" alt="Nova Gallery - Responsive HTML5 Multimedia Gallery"></a>\n<br><br><a href="http://codecanyon.net/item/ccgallery-html5-multimedia-gallery/233741"><img src="http://1.s3.envato.com/files/35542452/ccgallery-preview.jpg" alt="CCGallery - HTML5 Multimedia Gallery"></a>\n<br><br><a href="http://codecanyon.net/item/vimuse-html5-media-player/7847349"><img src="https://0.s3.envato.com/files/115695856/vimuse-preview.jpg" alt="Vimuse - HTML5 Media Player"></a>', 'http://codecanyon.net/theme_previews/10800578-photo-feed-flow-gallery-exension', 'https://0.s3.envato.com/files/126468867/flowgallery-photofeed-preview.jpg', 'http://codecanyon.net/item/photo-feed-flow-gallery-exension/10800578', 'http://codecanyon.net/item/photo-feed-flow-gallery-exension/full_screen_preview/10800578', 8, 'albums, collections, extension, flickr, flow gallery, gallery, jquery, material design, photo, picasa, plugin, video', 0, 0, 0),
(67, 214, 'Sun Mar 15 10:42:46 +1100 2015', 'Tue Mar 17 14:43:23 +1100 2015', 'easy-row-duplication-jquery-plugin', 'easy Row Duplication - jQuery Plugin', '<h4 id="item-description__description">Description</h4>\neasy Row Duplication &ndash; jQuery plugin allows you to easily duplicate (and detete) rows in your HTML code.\n\n	The rows can contain anything you want: form items (input, textarea, checks, buttons), images, simple text, etc&hellip;\n\n\n	The only thing you have to do is to tell the plugin what HTML element you want to duplicate. Nothing else.\n\n\n	The plugin will allow you to customize almost anything. Following you&rsquo;ll find some of major features supported.\n\n\n<li>Multi language support (english and italian provided, but you can translate the plugin in your language in 15 seconds)</li>\n<li>Set the animation to show (and its speed) when adding a ros</li>\n<li>Set a limit to the number of the rows that can be added</li>\n<li>Customize the text, the position and the classes of the &ldquo;Add Row&rdquo; and &ldquo;Delete Row&rdquo; buttons. If you want to create your custom buttons, you can tell the plugin to use your ones instead of the default ones!</li>\n<li>Set the margin-top of each added row</li>\n<li>Call custom functions before/after a row add/delete</li>\n<li>Sortable rows using drag-and-drop (requires jQuery UI)</li>\nOf course you can have as many plugin as you want in your page and integrate very easily with your existing HTML structure!\n\n\n	In the demo I&rsquo;ve used a Bootstrap base, but you can use everything you want: from a very basic HTML structure up to the best and complex template you can find on the internet.\n\n\n	You will find the Docs inside the file after the download. Should you need further assistence, feel free to contact me <img src="/images/smileys/wink.png" alt=";)" title=";)">\n\n\n \n\n<h4 id="item-description__changelog">Changelog</h4>\nver. 1.0.0 (13-03-2015)\n<li>First relase</li>\n\n\nver. 1.1.0 (16-03-2015)\n<li>Added support for drag-and-drop. Rows can now be moved up and/or down. <strong>Requires jQueryUI!</strong></li>\n<li>Small improvements</li>\n', 'http://codecanyon.net/theme_previews/10756407-easy-row-duplication-jquery-plugin', 'https://0.s3.envato.com/files/126439064/590x300_flat.png', 'http://codecanyon.net/item/easy-row-duplication-jquery-plugin/10756407', 'http://codecanyon.net/item/easy-row-duplication-jquery-plugin/full_screen_preview/10756407', 5, 'add rows, dom, form, html, javascript, jquery, jquery plugin, rows, sortable', 0, 0, 0),
(68, 214, 'Thu Mar 19 01:40:45 +1100 2015', 'Sat Mar 28 04:11:38 +1100 2015', 'instalink-responsive-instagram-widget', 'InstaLink - Responsive Instagram Widget', '<img src="http://elfsight.com/instalink/codecanyon_images/instalink-description-2.png" alt="InstaLink - Responsive Instagram Widget Description">\n\n\n<h2 id="item-description__instalink-features">InstaLink Features</h2>\n<h4 id="item-description__widget-includes">Widget includes</h4>\n<li>Images from Instagram username or hashtag</li>\n<li>Profile info (profile picture, images and quantity of followers)</li>\n<li>Button followed to your Instagram profile page</li>\n<h4 id="item-description__design-amp-ui">Design &amp; UI</h4>\n<li>Fully responsive and mobile friendly</li>\n<li>Support high-resolution displays (retina ready)</li>\n<li>Images adapt to any size of widget</li>\n<li>Beautiful loading animations</li>\n<li>Fast loading</li>\n<li>Images cache</li>\n<h4 id="item-description__customization">Customization</h4>\n<li>4 sizes of images (small, medium, large, xlarge).</li>\n<li>Branding opportunity. Choose your own colors for panel, button and text.</li>\n<li>Fully customizable via HTML and CSS.</li>\n<li>Well documented JS code.</li>\n<h4 id="item-description__install-amp-support">Install &amp; Support</h4>\n<li>Easy and fast installation in your website. </li>\n<li>Super easy to use for beginners. Just add one tag!</li>\n<li>Code generator. Configure your widget and get the code. <a href="http://elfsight.com/instalink/" rel="nofollow">Try it here</a>.</li>\n<li>Very detailed documentation with examples.</li>\n<li>Free and fast support via email, skype or comments.</li>\n<br><h2 id="item-description__try-widget-on-mobile-device">Try widget on mobile device</h2>\n<img src="http://elfsight.com/instalink/codecanyon_images/instalink-mobile-qr.png"><br><h2 id="item-description__changelog-new-version-1-1-0-is-available-for-download">Changelog &ndash; <strong>new version 1.1.0 is available for download</stron