(141, 216, 'Fri Mar 20 10:02:44 +1100 2015', 'Fri Mar 27 06:58:54 +1100 2015', 'chow-recipe-food-wordpress-theme', 'Chow - Recipe & Food WordPress Theme', '<a href="http://chow.purethe.me/" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://purethemes.wpengine.com/things/chow/chow-demo-1.png"></a> &Acirc;&nbsp;<a href="http://chow.purethe.me/boxed-version/" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://purethemes.wpengine.com/things/chow/chow-demo-2.png"></a>\n\n\n	Chow is a genuinely culinary WordPress Theme. This recipe theme will let you share all your recipes and cooking tips with wide audience. Chow comes with Schema.org support. It means that your blog will be understand not only by people, but also by search engines.\n\n\n	<a href="http://themeforest.net/item/chow-recipe-food-wordpress-theme/10802589/support"><img src="http://purethemes.net/branding/new/support.png"></a><a href="http://www.docs.purethemes.net/chow/" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://purethemes.net/branding/new/docs.png"></a><a href="http://www.purethemes.net/" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://purethemes.net/branding/new/newsletter.png"></a><a href="http://themeforest.net/user/purethemes/follow"><img src="http://purethemes.net/branding/new/follow.png"></a>\n\n\nLatest version: Chow 1.1; FoodiePress 1.2\n\n<h2 id="item-description__support-for-micoformats-and-google-recipe-view"><strong>Support for Micoformats and Google Recipe View</strong></h2>\nschema.org is a collaboration by Google, Microsoft, and Yahoo! to improve the web by creating a structured data markup schema supported by major search engines. On-page markup helps search engines understand the information on webpages and provide richer results. Learn more on www.schema.org.\n\n	&Acirc;&nbsp;\n<img src="http://purethe.me/things/chow/chow_01.png">\n\n\n<h2 id="item-description__foodiepress-recipe-editor"><strong>FoodiePress Recipe Editor</strong></h2>\n\n	Chow comes with FoodiePress plugin &ndash; unique solution for creating and managing Recipe data in WordPress, allowing for advanced search by ingredients, customizable layouts and templates for recipe, print styles and many many features.\n\n\n	<img src="http://purethe.me/things/chow/chow_desc_02.png">\n\n\n<h2 id="item-description__advanced-search"><strong>Advanced Search</strong></h2>\nThis is special page which allows your visitors to search all your recipes by including and/or excluding ingredients and narrowing search results by many custom taxonomies like level of recipe or time required to do it. Your visitos can type to search box anything they have in the fridge, get results, print choosen recipe and start cooking.\n\n	&Acirc;&nbsp;\n<img src="http://purethe.me/things/chow/chow_desc_03.png">\n\n\n<h3 id="item-description__theme-features">Theme features</h3> <li>Recipe creator helping to create valid schema.org recipes</li>\n<li>Front-end submit and edit pages for registered users</li>\n<li><a href="http://chow.purethe.me/chow-dashboard/" rel="nofollow">Chow Dashboard</a></li>\n<li>Reviews system</li>\n<li>Favourite posts for registered and anonymous users</li>\n<li>HTML5 &amp; CSS3</li> \n<li>Responsive design</li> \n<li>support for hRecipe and Schema.org</li>\n<li>3 layouts to display posts (grid view, excerpt mode and full posts) </li> \n<li>Left or right sidebar</li> \n<li>Recipe creator</li>\n<li>4 Designs</li>\n<li>Localization (.po and .mo file)</li> \n<li>Shortcodes, page templates</li> \n<li>Create your own custom colour scheme</li> <li>Change fonts</li> <li>..and more</li> <br><br><h3 id="item-description__do-you-miss-any-feature">Do you miss any feature?</h3> Ask me to do it, I&rsquo;m constantly looking for ways to improve my themes.<br><br><h3 id="item-description__changelog">Changelog</h3>\n<pre>\nVersion 1.1:\n* fixed print styleshet\n* added support for PrintFriendly printing (doesn''t require plugin, added by default, can be disabled in Settings -&gt; FoodiePress)\n* added Users Dashboard with list of added posts and list of favourite posts\n* added option to Edit posts from front-end\n* Video posts format http://chow.purethe.me/2015/03/06/choclate-cake-with-green-tea-cream/\n* fix for WooCommerce 2.3.7\n* option to show Recipe summary instead of Post Content on List View\n* improved slider (different button for standard post and option to change fonts)\n* added compatibility for RevolutionSlider (plugin is not included)\n* added shortcode [posts_grid]\n* lightbox in recipe gallery\n</pre>', 'http://themeforest.net/theme_previews/10802589-chow-recipe-food-wordpress-theme', 'https://0.s3.envato.com/files/126488540/screenshots/01.__large_preview.png', 'http://themeforest.net/item/chow-recipe-food-wordpress-theme/10802589', 'http://themeforest.net/item/chow-recipe-food-wordpress-theme/full_screen_preview/10802589', 58, 'chef, cook, cooking, culinary, eat, food, foodies, health, ingredients, meal, microformats, recipe, recipes, schema.org', 0, 0, 0),
